President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals for key administration posts. The nominees include Carlos Pascual for Ambassador to Mexico, David Jacobson for Ambassador to Canada, Brigadier General James B. Smith for Ambassador to the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, Donald Gips for Ambassador to the Republic of South Africa, Patricia N. Moller for Ambassador to the Republic of Guinea, Nicole A. Avant for Ambassador to the Commonwealth of the Bahamas, Kenneth H. Merten for Ambassador to the Republic of Haiti, and Anne E. Derse for Ambassador to the Republic of Lithuania. President Obama expressed gratitude for these individuals who will represent the United States abroad during this important time. Each nominee brings a depth of experience, and the President looks forward to working with them in the future.